{
  "text": "One thing I don't understand is why, if there was no veil, that the review of incarnation after the incarnation would help the process, since it seems to me that the entity should already be aware of what was happening. Possibly this has to do with the nature of space-time and time space. Could you clear that up, please? I am more. It is true that the nature of time space is such that a lifetime may be seen whole as a book or record of the pages studied, riffled through and reread. However, the value of a review is that of the attesting as opposed to the studying at the attesting when the attest is true, the distillations of all study are made clear during the process of a study which you may call the incarnation, regardless of an entity's awareness of the process taking a place. The material is diffused, and over attention is almost inevitably placed upon a detail, the attesting upon the assessation of the incarnative estate is not that testing which involves the correct memorization of many details. This testing is a rather the observing of self by self, often with aid, as we have said. An attitude or complex of attitudes which bias the consciousness of the mind, body, spirit.",
